properties.otherAdvice:
Road closures and parking restrictions will be in place for Australia Day events in the city and Milsons Point. Up to 65,000 people are expected to attend evening events at Circular Quay. 

Key road closures:

  • 4am to midnight: George St from Essex St to Hickson Rd. George St between Hickson Rd and Lower Fort St will remain closed until 10PM Monday 27 Jan for The Rocks Markets trading.
  • 7am to midnight: Hickson Rd from George St to Pottinger St.
  • 7am to 10am: Hickson Rd from Napoleon St to Towns Place (for 10km wheelchair race).
  • 7am to 11am: Hickson Rd from Towns Place to Pottinger St (for 10km wheelchair race).
  • 4pm to midnight: roads north of Bridge St including sections of Alfred St, Albert St, George St, Pitt St, Loftus St, Young St & Phillip St.
  • 7.30pm to 10.30pm: Cahill Expressway lanes 7 & 8 and Circular Quay Overpass, Lane 4 on the Harbour Bridge.
  • 8.30pm to 10.30pm: Macquarie St north of Bridge St, Grosvenor St/Bridge St from York St to Macquarie St and sections of George St and Bond St. Note: no access to/from Opera House Wilson Carpark during this time 

Note: The speed limit will be reduced to 40km/hr on the Harbour Bridge from 8pm to 9:30pm. Cahill Expressway Overpass walkway will be closed from 4pm to 9:30pm. Sydney Harbour Bridge Walkway and Cycleway will remain open.

Special event clearway parking restrictions will be in effect on roads around Circular Quay and The Rocks from 3am with additional clearways in place from 2pm on most major roads in the Sydney CBD until midnight.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones, even for local residents or RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.

properties.otherAdvice:
Large crowds are expected to attend the first concert at Bankwest Stadium for the Cold Chisel Blood Moon Tour from 5pm.

Traffic will be heavier than usual on O'Connell St, Parramatta Rd, Church St, Victoria Rd, James Ruse Dr and Pennant Hills Rd as large crowds travel to the stadium during Friday evening peak. Motorists should plan to arrive early and allow extra travel time.

Roads around the stadium will close prior to the end of the concert and reopen once crowds have safely cleared the precinct including:

- O’Connell St from Grose St to George St

- Ross St from O’Connell St to Trott St

- Victoria Rd from O’Connell St to Villiers St

Motorists are advised to allow plenty of extra travel time and detour around the closures via Parkes St, Harris St, Macarthur St and Isabella St or Victoria Rd instead to avoid delays.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Summer Holiday Period - SHOALHAVEN Naval College Rd, Booderee Ave, Cyrus St at Northern Hyams Beach
properties.otherAdvice:
Changed traffic conditions and speed reductions are in place approaching Hyams Beach including one-way roads at the northern end of Hyams Beach to manage the heavy traffic over the busy summer holiday period until 27 January.

  • A temporary roundabout will be in operation on Cnr Naval College Rd and Booderee Ave from 7am to 6pm daily.
  • Speed reduction from 80km/h to 40km/h will be in effect along Naval College Rd approaching Booderee Ave in both directions.
  • One way traffic changes will be in place on Tulip St (northbound only), Cyrus St (southbound only), Bamboo Ave (westbound only) and Anemone Ave (eastbound only).

If Hyams Beach reaches capacity, or in the event of a catastrophic fire danger rating, temporary closures at Naval College Rd and Booderee Ave will be implemented.

Motorists should arrive early or expect significant delays on roads approaching the township and beach during this period. Alternative white sand beaches can be found at Website: Shoalhaven – South Coast NSW

properties.headline: March - Sunday 26 January - SYDNEY CBD TO CAMPERDOWN Elizabeth St, Pitt St, Broadway and City Rd
properties.publicTransport: Buses will be diverting while roads are closed. Check service alerts for the latest info at transportnsw.info.
properties.otherAdvice:
Up to 10,000 people are expected to take part in a planned march. The group will gather in Hyde Park South from 11am before taking to the road at around midday travelling to Victoria Park by about 2:30pm.

Road closures will be in place between 11:45am and 2:30pm approximately on sections of Liverpool St, Elizabeth St, Hay St, Eddy Ave, Pitt St, George St and surrounding roads.

NSW Police will escort the march and reopen roads progressively as the group travels along the route. 

Motorists travelling from the city toward the Inner West will be detoured via Park St, Oxford St, Cleveland St, City Rd south and join Parramatta Rd via Missenden Rd. 

Motorists travelling to the city from Parramatta Rd can continue via the eastbound lanes of Broadway, but delays are expected.

HYDE PARK SOUTH, SYDNEY CBD TO VICTORIA PARK, CAMPERDOWN

properties.headline: !Disregard But Do Not Delete! - BROKEN HILL Blende Street
Australia Day in Parramatta - Sunday 26 January - PARRAMATTA O'Connell St at Parramatta Park
properties.publicTransport: Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
Large crowds are expected to attend Australia Day events at Parramatta Park throughout the day from 6am until 9.15pm.

Parramatta Park is vehicle-free on Australia Day, there will no access for vehicle traffic until midnight. 

Lane 1 northbound on O’Connell St at George St will be closed from 7pm until 11pm to allow for crowds to safely leave the park after the festivities.

A pick up and drop off zone will be managed along lanes 1 and 2 on Pitt St between Hunter St and Macquarie St from 6am to 11pm. The speed limit will also be reduced to 40km/h along this section of Pitt St, Macquarie St and O’Connell St to Victoria Rd.

Motorists should allow extra travel time and consider alternate routes.
properties.displayName: Australia Day in Parramatta - Sunday 26 January

properties.headline: Australia Day at The Entrance - Sunday 26 January - THE ENTRANCE The Entrance Rd, Marine Pde and Coral St approaching Memorial Park
properties.otherAdvice:
Up to 15,000 people are expected to attend Australia Day celebrations at Memorial Park in The Entrance from 2pm until 9pm.

Sections of Marine Pde, Coral St East, Victoria Ave, The Entrance Rd and Beach Rd will be closed between 4pm and 10pm. Local diversions will be in place and resident access will be maintained when possible. 

Coral St West and Torrens Ave will also be under traffic control. The Marine Parade car park will be closed from midnight Saturday 25 January until 10pm on Sunday 26 January. 

Traffic is expected to be heavier than normal along the Central Coast Hwy as crowds make their way to and from the event.

Motorists should allow extra travel time and be aware of changed traffic conditions in the area.

properties.headline: Australia Day at Lake Macquarie - Saturday 25 and Sunday 26 January - CROUDACE BAY AND SPEERS POINT Bareki Rd and The Esplanade approaching Thomas H Halton Park and Speers Point Park
properties.otherAdvice:
Large crowds are expected to attend various events in Lake Macquarie over the Australia Day weekend.

On Saturday up to 5,000 people are expected to attend a Breakfast & Fun Day at Thomas H Halton Park, Croudace Bay from 7:30am until midday. Other events will be held along the foreshore until 10.30pm. Traffic is expected to be heavier than normal on Bereki Rd throughout the day. 

On Sunday up to 2,000 people are expected to attend the Sunday Sessions event at Speers Point Park from 3pm until 7pm. Traffic is expected to be heavier than normal on the Esplanade throughout the event.

Motorists should allow additional travel time and be aware of increased increased pedestrian activity on roads around the parks.

properties.headline: Royal National Park - Saturday 25 to Monday 27 January - ROYAL NATIONAL PARK McKell Ave, Farnell Ave and various roads at Princes Hwy
properties.otherAdvice:
The Royal National Park is typically very busy during the Australia Day long weekend from Saturday 25 to Monday 27 January.

Road closures will be implemented as precincts and car parks reach full at Wattamolla Beach, Garie Beach, Audley, Maianbar and Bundeena.

If parking capacity is reached across all precincts, traffic will only be permitted to travel through the park. If there are significant delays, both the northern and southern entries to the park via Farnell Ave at Loftus and via Lady Wakehurst Dr at Otford will close. Entry will be maintained via McKell Ave at Waterfall for residents only. 

Visitors are encouraged to check the Royal National Park local alerts before travelling for updates on precinct access. Walking trails may also be closed due to fire bans and/or risks so plan ahead. 

Road closures when precincts reach capacity:

  • Wattamolla Rd between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Wattamolla Beach
  • Garie Rd between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Garie Beach
  • Maianbar Rd between Bundeena Dr and Maianbar township
  • Bundeena Dr between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Bundeena township

Traffic controllers and NSW Police will be on-site managing access for local residents on Maianbar Rd and Bundeena Dr upon proof of residential address.

properties.headline: ARMIDALE HAY RUN - ALBURY TO ARMIDALE Hume Hwy, M7, Pennant Hills Rd, M1, Hunter Exp, New England Hwy
properties.otherAdvice:
Burrumbuttock Hay Runners - Armidale Hay Run, Friday 24 and Saturday 25 January

A convoy of 180 trucks and support vehicles will be travelling from Albury to Singleton on Friday, and then from Singleton to Armidale on Saturday, where traffic may be heavier than usual on Glen Innes Rd, Erskine St, Marsh St and nearby roads.

The convoy will travel in groups of approximately 20 vehicles at a time, from around 6am each day.

Motorists are reminded to exercise caution when overtaking the convoy, allow extra travel time and follow the direction of police.
